[normal]1.1  
[normal]              
[normal]As 
[normal]in 
[normal]many cities 
[normal]Greater Manchester has some of the busiest roads in the country
[normal]. The city
[normal] is a major hub for commercial activity and 
[normal]has 
[normal]been affected by 
[normal]the national increase in road user traffic. Whilst it has an increase in 
[normal]its fair share of heavy goods veh
[normal]ic
[normal]les and buses using these roads
[normal] it does not contain the 
[normal]amount of continuous 
[normal]structural 
[normal]development that the capital is experiencing.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.2
[normal]              
[normal]It is clear that Manchester does not have the motoring infrastructure which requires the constant monitoring from 
[normal]T
[normal]fL
[normal] to allow free flow of traffic and use of road users within the capital.
