[normal].3  
[normal]              
[normal]The
[normal] 
[normal]main 
[normal]offences 
[normal]committed are
[normal] careless and inconsiderate cycling,
[normal] failing to comply 
[normal]with traffic signs
[normal], 
[normal]cycling
[normal] with
[normal] no lights fitted or illuminated and cycling on 
[normal]the footpath
[normal].
[normal] A 
[normal]significant
[normal] number of collision
[normal]s
[normal] take place when a cyclist rides from the pavement into the road.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4
[normal].4  
[normal]              
[normal]Failing to comply with traffic signs can be red lights or one way streets. Cycling with
[normal] no lights fitted or illuminated is an offence, which can only
[normal] be dealt with during the hours 
[normal]of darkness. Cycling on the footpath is dealt with on a common sense approach
[normal] 
[normal]i.e.
[normal]: busy footpaths in town centres. The previous three can be dealt with by way of a traffic 
[normal]o
[normal]ffence report 
[normal]whilst
[normal] careless and inconsiderate cycling is a 
[normal]summonsable
[normal] offence and deemed more serious.
[normal] The only offence a PCSO can enforce is cycling on the foot
[normal]path all others have to be dealt with by a constable. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4
[normal].5  
[normal]              
[normal]Having chosen a suitable location 
[normal]the team of officers / staff working together to deliver the operation
[normal] observe
[normal] 
[normal]offenders, be it
[normal] 
[normal]cyclists or 
[normal]              
[normal]other road users, the details are forwarded to ‘sto
[normal]ppers’ who directs offenders to a safe location to stop.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.6
[normal]              
[normal]The offenders are 
[normal]spoken to by an officer. 
[normal]Vehicular offences are processed in the usual manner whilst 
[normal]the offending cyclist is issued
[normal] with 
[normal]a traffic offence report
[normal] 
[normal](
[normal]£
[normal]50
[normal] fine). 
[normal]              
[normal]As an alternati
[normal]ve to the fine t
[normal]he cyclists are then given the opportunity to 
[normal]attend 
[normal]a
[normal] force
[normal] cycle safety 
[normal]presentation
[normal] 
[normal]and 
[normal]informed 
[normal]upon conclusion of such 
[normal]the fine will be rescinded.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.7
[normal]  
[normal]              
[normal]This 
[normal]mirrors the current driver improvement scheme and is a onetime offer
[normal] and at this stage is free
[normal].  Cyclists are informed that if they commit a further offence this will result in a fine or court appearance. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4
[normal].
