[normal]8
[normal]              
[normal]Recommendations
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8.1
[normal]              
[normal]Most of the offences committed by cyclists are seen as low level and as such are not dealt with robustly. Consideration must be given to ex
[normal]panding the powers of the PCSO 
[normal]to include such offences as lighting and fail to conform to
[normal] traffic signs. Currently they 
[normal]can only issue 
[normal]a Traffic Offence Report
[normal] 
[normal]for the offence of cycling on the footpath.  This would fit th
[normal]e new 
[normal]recommendations of increasi
[normal]ng the use of neighbourhood policing
[normal] model and allow more cyclists to be educated
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8.2
[normal]              
[normal]Cycle retailers could do more to support the work of the local authorities, police and community groups by ensuring 
[normal]when 
[normal]they sell a cycle 
[normal]it is 
[normal]fitted with the 
[normal]respective lighting
[normal], security
[normal], (lock and cycle marking
[normal]) fluorescent
[normal] jacket
[normal] and 
[normal]advice on the rules of the road for cyclists
[normal], cycle maintenance 
[normal]together with
[normal] free cycling information
[normal] in with the purchase price.
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8.3
[normal]              
[normal]An N
[normal]DORS style
[normal] course similar to the dri
[normal]ver improvement scheme
[normal] should be developed
[normal]. (GMP 
[normal]is
[normal] 
[normal]currently compiling such for 
[normal]TfGM
[normal] to complete and offer of training for offences committed within the
[normal] 
[normal]force). This leaves the force to deal with enforcement and the local authority to train.
[normal] 
[normal]The aim eventually would be to look to a national course. 
[normal] This would also follow with
[normal] 
[normal]a training of police staff as to the new system in place.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8.4
[normal]              
[normal]Whilst there are many areas within Greater Manchester that are relatively safe to cycle 
[normal]              
[normal]there are a numbe
[normal]r of areas of concern
[normal]. The area highlighted is one that has been given 
[normal]              
[normal]government approval to change the road structure reducing the potential risk to 
[normal]              
[normal]cyclists.
[normal] 
[normal]However the traffic displaced may well 
[normal]create
[normal] another potential ‘hot spot.’
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]8.5
[normal]              
[normal]Despite the
[normal] number of HGV’s on the road system to prohibit such at peak times would 
[normal]              
[normal]not be feasible for the following reasons.
